             deposed, that the Beadle of the Ward and another came to him (this Evidence), the next Morning, and told him of the Accident, saying it would be some charge; and that if he (this Evidence) would contribute some Money for burying the Boy and paying the Coroner, there should be no Prosecution, for they knew no Body, and would not find the Man. He farther deposed, that the Prisoner was of a Gentle and Peaceable Temper. The Jury considering the matter, found him <rs id="t17210419-62-verdict325" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17210419-62-verdict325" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
